Installation

  • Download the extension via Shopware Store
  • Install it via Plugin Manager

Configuration

Configuration takes completely place in shopware backend plugin config via plugin manager.

General

Include FontAwesome

Include FontAwesome 4.7.0 ( http://fontawesome.io/ ) from CDN to display nice icons for the social login buttons. Disable it if you already have included FontAwesome or want to override default styling.

Country Fallback

Select the country which should be used if the plugin cannout determine a country for the customer during social login. A country is mandatory
for the customer so you should select the country here.

Hybrid Auth

Debug Mode

You can choose one of the debug modes. The are the same as hybridauth library uses. You can read more about this here http://hybridauth.sourceforge.net/userguide/Debugging_and_Logging.html

Debug File

Enter the path where the debug file is located here.


Facebook

At first go to https://developers.facebook.com/ and register a new application.


Add new App-ID and enter your information



Add Facebook Login


Activate Client-OAuth-Anmeldung , Web-OAuth-Anmeldung and Browser Control Redirect and enter Valid OAuth Redirect URI .

This URL should look like:

  http://www.shopware-portrino.de/hybridauth?hauth_done=Facebook




Enabled

Set Facebook :: Enabled to Yes .

App-ID

Enter your App-ID, which you can find on your application dashboard into the field: â€œ Facebook :: App-ID â€.


App-Secret

Enter your App-Secret, which you can find on your application dashboard into the field: â€œ Facebook :: App-Secret â€.


Scope

Enter your custom scope in this textarea. More information to this topiccan be found here: https://developers.facebook.com/docs/facebook-login/permissions .

! Clear the cache after you have made configuration changes  !


Google

At first go to https://console.developers.google.com/ and create a new application.


Create Project




Wait until the project is created - this may take a while...


Go to Credentials and click Create credentials =>  OAuth client ID




Enter OAuth consent screen data



Create client ID and  en ter the name you wish to use and enter the authorised redirect URI .



This URL MUST look like this: 

  http://www.shopware-portrino.de/hybridauth?hauth_done

Store the client ID and client secret or copy it directly into your plugin configuration

! Enable Google+ API in your API console !


Enabled

Set Google :: Enabled to Yes .

Client-ID

Enter your Client-ID, which you can find on your application credentials section into the field: â€œGoogle :: Client-IDâ€.

Clientkey

Enter your Clientkey, which you can find on your application credentials section into the field: â€œGoogle :: Clientkeyâ€.

Scope

Enter custom scopes to retrieve more or less information from google by adding them here. More information can be found
here: https://developers.google.com/identity/protocols/googlescopes .

! Clear the cache after you have made configuration changes !


Amazon

First of all you have to use SSL to get amazon social login working !

At first go to https://sellercentral.amazon.com/gp/homepage.html and register a new application.

Register new application




Enter your data


Go to Web Settings and get the Client ID and Client Secret.

Enter the Allowed Return URL

This URL MUST look like this: 

  https://www.shopware-portrino.de/hybridauth?hauth.done=Amazon

Store the client ID and client secret or copy it directly into your plugin configuration.

Enabled

Set Amazon :: Enabled to Yes .

Client-ID

Enter your Client-ID, which you can find on your Web Settings section into the field: â€œAmazon :: Client-IDâ€.

Client Secret

Enter your Client Secret, which you can find on your Web Settings section into the field: â€œAmazon :: Client Secretâ€.

! Clear the cache after you have made configuration changes !
